<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, viewport-fit=cover">
  <title>Accessibility Statement (ADA) | GetPawsy</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
  <style>
    .legal-page { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 20px; }
    .legal-page h1 { color: var(--pawsy-primary, #6366f1); margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .legal-page .last-updated { color: #666; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 30px; }
    .legal-page h2 { color: #333; margin: 30px 0 15px; border-bottom: 2px solid #f0f0f0; padding-bottom: 10px; }
    .legal-page p, .legal-page li { line-height: 1.8; color: #444; }
    .legal-page ul { padding-left: 25px; margin: 15px 0; }
    .legal-page .highlight { background: #ecfdf5; padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 4px solid #10b981; margin: 20px 0; }
    .legal-page .accessibility-icon { font-size: 2rem; margin-right: 10px; }
    .legal-page .contact-box { background: #f0fdf4; padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px; margin: 20px 0; border: 2px solid #10b981; }
    .legal-page .feature-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0; }
    .legal-page .feature-card { background: #f8f9ff; padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px; }
    .legal-page .feature-card h4 { margin: 0 0 10px; color: #333; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('../partials/header') %>

  <main class="legal-page">
    <h1><span class="accessibility-icon">‚ôø</span> Accessibility Statement</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: December 2024</p>

    <div class="highlight">
      <p><strong>Our Commitment to Accessibility.</strong> GetPawsy is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>1. WCAG 2.1 AA Commitment</h2>
    <p>GetPawsy strives to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standards. These guidelines help make web content more accessible to people with a wide range of disabilities, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Visual impairments (blindness, low vision, color blindness)</li>
      <li>Hearing impairments</li>
      <li>Motor impairments</li>
      <li>Cognitive and learning disabilities</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Accessibility Features</h2>
    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>üîç Screen Reader Compatible</h4>
        <p>Our website is designed to work with screen readers like JAWS, NVDA, and VoiceOver.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>‚å®Ô∏è Keyboard Navigation</h4>
        <p>All functionality is accessible via keyboard for users who cannot use a mouse.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>üé® Color Contrast</h4>
        <p>We maintain sufficient color contrast ratios for text and interactive elements.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>üìù Alt Text</h4>
        <p>All images include descriptive alt text for screen reader users.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>üî§ Resizable Text</h4>
        <p>Text can be resized up to 200% without loss of content or functionality.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>üéØ Focus Indicators</h4>
        <p>Clear visual indicators show which element has keyboard focus.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>3. Assistive Technology Compatibility</h2>
    <p>Our website is designed to be compatible with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Screen Readers:</strong> JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver, TalkBack</li>
      <li><strong>Screen Magnifiers:</strong> ZoomText, Windows Magnifier</li>
      <li><strong>Speech Recognition:</strong> Dragon NaturallySpeaking, Voice Control</li>
      <li><strong>Keyboard-Only Navigation:</strong> Full site functionality without a mouse</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Browser Recommendations</h2>
    <p>For the best accessible experience, we recommend:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Google Chrome (latest version)</li>
      <li>Mozilla Firefox (latest version)</li>
      <li>Microsoft Edge (latest version)</li>
      <li>Apple Safari (latest version)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Alternative Communication Channels</h2>
    <p>If you have difficulty using our website, we offer alternative ways to shop and get support:</p>
    <div class="contact-box">
      <p><strong>üìß Email:</strong> accessibility@getpawsy.com</p>
      <p><strong>üìû Phone:</strong> Available upon request for assisted ordering</p>
      <p><strong>üí¨ Live Chat:</strong> Our Pawsy AI chatbot is available 24/7</p>
      <p>We will work with you to find an accessible solution to meet your needs.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>6. Ongoing Accessibility Efforts</h2>
    <p>We are committed to continuous improvement of accessibility:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Regular Audits:</strong> We conduct periodic accessibility audits of our website</li>
      <li><strong>Staff Training:</strong> Our team receives accessibility training</li>
      <li><strong>User Feedback:</strong> We actively incorporate feedback from users with disabilities</li>
      <li><strong>Third-Party Testing:</strong> We engage accessibility experts for independent reviews</li>
      <li><strong>Technology Updates:</strong> We stay current with accessibility best practices and technologies</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Known Limitations</h2>
    <p>While we strive for full accessibility, some areas may have limitations:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Some older product images may lack complete alt text (being updated)</li>
      <li>Third-party embedded content may not meet all accessibility standards</li>
      <li>PDF documents are being converted to accessible formats</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We are actively working to address these limitations.</p>

    <h2>8. Feedback & Complaints</h2>
    <p>We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of GetPawsy. If you encounter accessibility barriers or have suggestions for improvement:</p>
    <div class="contact-box">
      <p><strong>Email:</strong> accessibility@getpawsy.com</p>
      <p><strong>Subject Line:</strong> Accessibility Feedback</p>
      <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> We will respond within 5 business days</p>
      <p>Please include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Description of the accessibility barrier</li>
        <li>The URL of the page where you encountered the issue</li>
        <li>Your assistive technology (if applicable)</li>
        <li>Your preferred contact method</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>9. Legal Compliance</h2>
    <p>This accessibility statement reflects our commitment to comply with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA)</li>
      <li>Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act</li>
      <li>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA</li>
      <li>California Unruh Civil Rights Act</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>10. Statement Review</h2>
    <p>This accessibility statement was last reviewed in December 2024. We review and update this statement annually, or when significant changes are made to our website.</p>
  </main>

  <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
